Loup Basin Public Health Department
September 1 at 3:54 PM ¬∑

LBPHD District-Wide Risk Dial
Updated 9/1/2020

After two weeks in the orange, the dial has moved back to yellow. There continues to be community spread in Valley and Custer counties that if not stopped could tip the dial back into the orange. Other factors that figure into the risk dial calculation include healthcare capacity, testing availability, and the ability to conduct contact tracing efficiently.

For additional information about what the colors mean, please visit this link: https://d1d0577b-d026-4d96-b53c-c95b60643e79.filesusr.com/ugd/1addfa_01f5d2322c764115b2910bbfc8b066dc.pdf

Disclaimer: this risk dial is determined utilizing district wide data and may not represent an individual county's current status.

post_text: Pandemic Electronic Benefits Transfer (P-EBT)
shared_text:
Nebraska State Education Association
July 15 at 10:34 AM ¬∑

Nebraska has been approved for the Pandemic-EBT program! That means families that were on the Free or Reduced Price Lunch (FRPL) program for the 19-20 school year are eligible to receive the cost of meals missed because of COVID-19 school closures on an EBT card. Families eligible for FRPL for the full period of school closure will receive a total of $281 for the days closed per child. Deadline is July 19th! https://cip-dhhs.ne.gov/redcap/surveys/?s=DM3WNPMJN7

post_text:
Congratulations to Bailey Schneider the first recipient of the $500 John Green Mighty Bulldog scholarship. This new scholarship was created by John Green and Rhonda Blanford-Green for Sargent Public Schools seniors through the Bulldog Education Foundation. This award is presented to the candidate who displays outstanding character, good academics and involvement with athletics and activities while a student at Sargent High School. John said, ‚ÄùThere was an influential gentleman in the Sargent community many years ago by the name of K.W. Peterson. He once said to me, prior to leaving for college, "you will someday be judged based on your character and your willingness to give back to your community so don‚Äôt forget where you come from‚Äù. This scholarship is just a small token of thanks for a community that helped raise me.‚Äù
Bailey participated in Volleyball, Basketball, Track, FBLA, FFA, Pups Mentoring, One Acts, and Middle Loup 4-H Club. Bailey plans to attend Wayne State College and major in Elementary Education.

The Nebraska Department of Education is seeking feedback from all stakeholders to understand local needs as well as potential investments and supports. Please take a moment to complete this short survey, also available in Spanish: ¬≠¬≠https://nde.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_efislqh4QDEA1KZ. Additionally, please include this link with your communication to parents and families.

Deadline to complete this survey is Monday, May 11, 2020. Thanks

Matthew L. Blomstedt, Ph.D.
Commissioner of Education
